d eager to share what we know and learn in-turn.\r\n\r\nI firmly believe that humans\' greatest invention to this date is to build the art of communication. For, that was one remarkable achievement which helped us express our emotions and develop relations. I am hoping this blog would help us communicate our thoughts in design and stay in touch with you.','Hello and Welcome to Divami\'s Blog','','inherit','closed','closed','','32-revision-v1','','','2016-05-19 09:14:10','2016-05-19 09:14:10','',32,'http://www.divami.com/blog/32-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(57,3,'2016-07-21 15:46:19','2016-07-21 10:16:19','<label>Subscribe and receive notifications of new posts by email.</label>\r\n<input type=\"email\" name=\"EMAIL\" placeholder=\"Your email address\" required>\r\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Subscribe\">','','','publish','closed','closed','','57','','','2016-07-21 15:46:19','2016-07-21 10:16:19','',0,'http://www.divami.com/blog/mc4wp-form/57/',0,'mc4wp-form','',0),(59,2,'2016-05-30 14:47:44','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p>\r\n	<label>Email address: </label>\r\n	<input type=\"email\" name=\"EMAIL\" placeholder=\"Your email address\" required />\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n	<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Sign up\" />\r\n</p>','','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2016-05-30 14:47:44','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://www.divami.com/blog/?post_type=mc4wp-form&p=59',0,'mc4wp-form','',0),(76,1,'2016-09-19 15:23:51','2016-09-19 09:53:51','<h2>Deep Linking</h2>\r\nDeep linking is the usage of the URL, which will take to specific page (content) directly without traversing application from home page [1]. It helps in getting indexed so that these links can be easily searchable by search engines like Google, Yahoo.. etc.\r\n\r\n<strong>Examples for deep linking urls</strong>:\r\n<a href=\"http://www.divami.com/blog/deep-linking-angular/\">http://www.divami.com/blog/deep-linking-angular/</a>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/groups/4314060/profile\">https://www.linkedin.com/groups/4314060/profile</a>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/JavaScript/113124472034820\">https://www.facebook.com/pages/JavaScript/113124472034820</a>\r\n<h2>Deep Linking in Angular</h2>\r\n<strong>With ‘#’</strong>:\r\nAngular by default supports deep linking using <strong>‘#’</strong>.\r\nEx: <a href=\"https://www.deeplinking.com#/deep/linking\">https://www.deeplinking.com#/deep/linking</a>\r\n\r\nIt has following drawbacks\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Search engines (SEO) don’t recognise the url after ‘#’, so the page full path does not get indexed.</li>\r\n 	<li>Google analytics also don’t capture the url after ‘#’, so we may not get accurate results.</li>\r\n 	<li>Readability of the url will not be that good.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Removing ‘#’</strong>:\r\nWe have to do following changes in angular application code to get rid of ‘#’ in url.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><strong>Enable html5Mode</strong>:\r\nWe have to enable <em><code>$locationProvider.html5Mode(true).hashPrefix(‘!’)</code></em> in angular config function. Some browsers don’t support html5Mode, so we need to add hashPrefix(‘!’).\r\n<pre>angular.module(\'appModule\').config([\'$localStorageProvider\', function($localStorageProvider) {\r\n    <strong>$locationProvider.html5Mode(true).hashPrefix(‘!’);</strong>\r\n}]);\r\n</pre>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Loading files</strong>: Generally in HTML header we include files as <code>&lt;script src=\"vendor/angular.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code>.  After enabling html5Mode, these files will not be loaded correctly. To fix this we have to set <code>&lt;base href=\"/\"&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;script src=\"/vendor/angular.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code>\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: If you mention href value as <strong>‘/’</strong>, it will refer to server base url. If you want to point to other domain path for example in local host, it will not work with <strong>‘/’</strong>, so we need to mention it as <code>&lt;base href=\"http://localhost/appFolder/\" /&gt;</code></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Enabling Redirection</strong>: Reload &amp; Refresh will not work after <strong>html5Mode</strong> is enabled, because browser will check for folders and it leads to  <code>404 Page Not Found </code>error. To get it worked we need to redirect to <code>index.html</code> file, for that we have to add the following in <code>.htaccess</code> file (or in sever configuration)[2]:\r\n<pre>RewriteEngine on\r\n\r\n# Don\'t rewrite files or directories\r\nRewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -f [OR]\r\nRewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -d\r\nRewriteRule ^ - [L]\r\n\r\n # Rewrite everything else to index.html to allow html5 state links\r\nRewriteRule ^ index.html [L]\r\n</pre>\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: If you are using <code>debug.html</code> for development and <code>index.html</code> for production, then you have to redirect to debug.html in development phase and index.html in production phase.</li>\r\n 	<li>You need to remove <strong>‘#’s</strong> before urls if you use any. For example we use like <code>&lt;a href=\"#deep/linking\"&gt;Deep Linking&lt;/a&gt;</code> when we use $routeProvider. In such href links we need to remove \"#\"</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>References</strong>:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deep_linking\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deep_linking</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"https://github.com/angular-ui/ui-router/wiki/Frequently-Asked-Questions#how-to-configure-your-server-to-work-with-html5mode\">https://github.com/angular-ui/ui-router/wiki/Frequently-Asked-Questions#how-to-configure-your-server-to-work-with-html5mode</a></li>\r\n</ol>','Deep Linking in Angular','','publish','open','open','','deep-linking-angular','','','2016-09-30 18:00:42','2016-09-30 12:30:42','',0,'http://www.divami.com/blog/?p=76',0,'post','',0),(77,1,'2016-07-03 13:00:04','2016-07-03 07:30:04','<div><b>Deep linking URL</b>: We need show full url which will tell where you are in the website.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><b>Ex</b>: <a href=\"https://nestor.divami.com/people/narendra\" target=\"_blank\">https://nestor.divami.com/people/narendra</a></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><b>Deep Linking in Angular with #</b>:</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Angular by default supports deep linking using <b>#.</b></div>\r\n<div><b> </b></div>\r\n<div><b>Ex</b>: <a href=\"https://nestor.divami.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://nestor.divami.com</a><b>#</b>/people/narendra</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><b>Problems with # in urls</b>:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>SEO engines won\'t recognize the url after <b>#</b>, so the website ranking may decrease</li>\r\n 	<li>Google Analytics won\'t capture the url after # for page views. So we may not get results as we want</li>\r\n 	<li>The readability of the url will decrease</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><b>Deep Linking in Angular without #</b>:</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>Deep linking without # is supported by Angular using <b>html5Mode</b> enabled. Following steps need to follow:</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><b>1. Enable html5Mode :</b></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>In the <b>config </b>of the application you have to enable html5Mode. In general the code will look like:</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>app.config([\'$stateProvider\', \'$urlRouterProvider\', \'$locationProvider\',</div>\r\n<div>    function( $stateProvider, $urlRouterProvider, $locationProvider) {</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>        $stateProvider</div>\r\n<div>.state(\'home\', {</div>\r\n<div>\'abstract\': true,</div>\r\n<div>templateUrl: \"partial.html\",</div>\r\n<div>controller: \"Ctrl\",</div>\r\n<div>url: \'/home\'</div>\r\n<div>});</div>\r\n<div>$urlRouterProvider.otherwise(\'/home\');</div>\r\n<div><b>$locationProvider.html5Mode(true).hashPrefix(\'!\');</b></div>\r\n<div>}</div>\r\n<div>]);</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Some browsers don\'t support <b>html5Mode</b>, for that we need to add <b>hashPrefix(\'!\')</b>.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><b>2. Loading files:</b></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Generally in header we used to include file as follows:</div>\r\n<div>&lt;script<b> src=\"vendor/jquery/jquery-1.10.2.js\"</b>&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>After enabling html5Mode, file may not load correctly. To fix this we have to use <b>&lt;base&gt;</b> tag.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><b>Ex</b>: &lt;base href=\"/\" /&gt;</div>\r\n<div><b> </b></div>\r\n<div>If you mention href value as \"/\", it will refer to server url. If you want to point to different url, you can change href.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><b>Note</b>: In localhost, it do not work with <b>\"/\"</b>, You need to mention full url till project folder.</div>\r\n<div><b>Ex</b>: &lt;base href=\"<a href=\"http://localhost/appFolder/\" target=\"_blank\">http://localhost/appFolder/</a>\" /&gt;</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><b>3. Enabling Redirection or Reload or Refresh:</b></div>\r\n<div><b> </b></div>\r\n<div>After enabling html5Mode, If you load \"<b><i><a href=\"https://nestor.divami.com/people/narendra\" target=\"_blank\">https://nestor.divami.com/people/narendra</a></i></b>\", browser will look for <b>people folder</b> and then <b>narendra folder</b> in people folder.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>It leads to url not found. To fix this we need to add .htacces file in server. The htaccess file will look like (<a href=\"https://github.com/angular-ui/ui-router/wiki/Frequently-Asked-Questions#how-to-configure-your-server-to-work-with-html5mode\" target=\"_blank\">link</a>):</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><b>RewriteEngine on</b></div>\r\n<div><b> </b></div>\r\n<div><b># Don\'t rewrite files or directories</b></div>\r\n<div><b>RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -f [OR]</b></div>\r\n<div><b>RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -d</b></div>\r\n<div><b>RewriteRule ^ - [L]</b></div>\r\n<div><b> </b></div>\r\n<div><b># Rewrite everything else to index.html to allow html5 state links</b></div>\r\n<div><b>RewriteRule ^ index.html [L]</b></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><b>Note</b>: For development which as minification enabled, please change <b>index.html</b> to <b>debug.html</b></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>we need to remove #s before partial html urls when we use  $routeProvider</div>\r\nThis is not needed if we use ui-router</div>','Angular Deep Linking','','inherit','closed','closed','','76-revision-v1','','','2016-07-03 13:00:04','2016-07-03 07:30:04','',76,'http://www.divami.com/blog/76-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(78,1,'2016-07-04 16:09:31','2016-07-04 10:39:31','<div id=\"wmd-preview-section-2\" class=\"wmd-preview-section preview-content\">\r\n<h2 id=\"deep-linking\">Deep Linking</h2>\r\nDeep linking is the usage of the URL, which will take to specific page (content) directly without traversing application from home page [1]. It helps easily searchable and indexed in search engines like Google, Yahoo &amp; etc.\r\n\r\n<strong>Good examples for deep linking are</strong>:\r\n<a href=\"http://www.divami.com/blog/angular-deep-linking/\">http://www.divami.com/blog/angular-deep-linking/</a>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/groups/4314060/profile\">https://www.linkedin.com/groups/4314060/profile</a>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/JavaScript/113124472034820\">https://www.facebook.com/pages/JavaScript/113124472034820</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"wmd-preview-section-3\" class=\"wmd-preview-section preview-content\">\r\n<h2 id=\"deep-linking-in-angular\">Deep Linking in Angular</h2>\r\n<strong>With ‘#’</strong>:\r\nAngular by default supports deep linking using ‘<strong>#</strong>‘.\r\nEx: <a href=\"https://www.deeplinking.com/#/deep/linking\">https://www.deeplinking.com#/deep/linking</a>\r\n\r\nWe have drawbacks with this deep linking\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Search engines (SEO) don’t recognise the url after ‘#’, so the page full path won’t indexed.</li>\r\n 	<li>Google analytics also don’t capture the u