line-height: normal;font-size: 18px;text-indent: 0px;text-align: left;letter-spacing: normal;float: none;direction: ltr;max-width: none;max-height: none;min-width: 0px;min-height: 0px;border: 0px;padding: 0px;margin: 0px\"><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\">urlRouterProvider.otherwise(‘/home′);</span></span>locationProvider.html5Mode(true).hashPrefix(‘!’);\r\n}\r\n]);\r\n\r\nSome browsers don’t support html5Mode, for that we need to add hashPrefix(‘!’).\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Loading files:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nGenerally in header we used to include file as follows:\r\n\r\nAfter enabling html5Mode, file may not load correctly. To fix this we have to use tag.\r\n\r\nEx:\r\n\r\nIf you mention href value as “/”, it will refer to server url. If you want to point to different url, you can change href.\r\n\r\nNote: In localhost, it do not work with “/”, You need to mention full url till project folder.\r\nEx:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Enabling Redirection or Reload or Refresh:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nAfter enabling html5Mode, If you load “<a href=\"https://nestor.divami.com/people/narendra\">https://nestor.divami.com/people/narendra</a>“, browser will look for people folder and then narendra folder in people folder.\r\n\r\nIt leads to url not found. To fix this we need to add .htacces file in server. The htaccess file will look like (link):\r\n\r\nRewriteEngine on\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"wmd-preview-section-4\" class=\"wmd-preview-section preview-content\">\r\n<h1 id=\"dont-rewrite-files-or-directories\">Don’t rewrite files or directories</h1>\r\nRewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -f [OR]\r\nRewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -d\r\nRewriteRule ^ - [L]\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"wmd-preview-section-5\" class=\"wmd-preview-section preview-content\">\r\n<h1 id=\"rewrite-everything-else-to-indexhtml-to-allow-html5-state-links\">Rewrite everything else to index.html to allow html5 state links</h1>\r\nRewriteRule ^ index.html [L]\r\n\r\nNote: For development which as minification enabled, please change index.html to debug.html\r\nwe need to remove #s before partial html urls when we use $routeProvider\r\nThis is not needed if we use ui-router\r\n\r\nReferences:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deep_linking\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deep_linking</a>\r\n\r\n</div>','Angular Deep Linking','','inherit','closed','closed','','76-revision-v1','','','2016-07-04 16:09:31','2016-07-04 10:39:31','',76,'http://www.divami.com/blog/76-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(79,1,'2016-07-04 23:42:16','2016-07-04 18:12:16','<h2 id=\"deep-linking\">Deep Linking</h2>\r\nDeep linking is the usage of the URL, which will take to specific page (content) directly without traversing application from home page [1]. It helps in easily searchable and indexed in search engines like Google, Yahoo &amp; etc.\r\n\r\n<strong>Examples for deep linking urls</strong>:\r\n<a href=\"http://www.divami.com/blog/angular-deep-linking/\">http://www.divami.com/blog/angular-deep-linking/</a>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/groups/4314060/profile\">https://www.linkedin.com/groups/4314060/profile</a>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/JavaScript/113124472034820\">https://www.facebook.com/pages/JavaScript/113124472034820</a>\r\n<h2 id=\"deep-linking-in-angular\">Deep Linking in Angular</h2>\r\n<strong>With ‘#’</strong>:\r\nAngular by default supports deep linking using <strong>‘#’</strong>.\r\nEx: <a href=\"https://www.deeplinking.com#/deep/linking\">https://www.deeplinking.com#/deep/linking</a>\r\n\r\nIt has following drawbacks\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Search engines (SEO) don’t recognise the url after ‘#’, so the page full path don’t indexed.</li>\r\n 	<li>Google analytics also don’t capture the url after ‘#’, so we may not get results as we want.</li>\r\n 	<li>Readability will decrease</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Removing ‘#’</strong>:\r\nWe have to do following to get out of ‘#’ in url.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><strong>Enable html5Mode</strong>: We have to enable this in application config file.\