ybe UI was not a big problem considering the other problems they were facing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">So, if we had judged the responses on their face value, we might have reached an unfavourable conclusion that could have derailed the design effort. We haven\'t done that but did a detailed route-cause analysis to understand the core issues. In this effort, we have consciously involved the stakeholders and that did help us immensely.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 class=\"p1\">Conclusion</h4>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">With all my experience, what I understood is, Users are extremely intelligent. They specifically know what they want and how they want. The only thing they do not know is, how to address them. It is us designers job to raise our hands and respond to the occasion.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Coming back to the opening quote, the responders subtly told that they need to travel quick, and they felt faster horses would help the cause. So, if the guy who made the statement did get a request for ‘faster horses’, then it is entirely up to him what to do with such a request. Whether to get into horse breeding or build carts with something that does a better job. The smarter choice leads to a greater product revolution.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">The users create the ideas; it is up to the presenter how well he can perceive the need and fulfil it.</p>','','','inherit','closed','closed','','86-revision-v1','','','2016-07-18 01:04:15','2016-07-17 19:34:15','',86,'http://www.divami.com/blog/86-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(115,1,'2016-07-18 01:08:32','2016-07-17 19:38:32','<blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">If I had asked people what they wanted, they would have said faster horses</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><i>Allegedly said by Henry Ford, which seems very unlikely</i></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">I am uncomfortable with the essence of this statement. It appears to be hinting that users do not know what they want. I disagree with that thought.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">As a designe