pan>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Host app (Hybrid app, written in Ionic JS)</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Share extension native app</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">With this approach, we can avoid app crashes. It works perfectly for all the images of size less than 20MB.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">When we install the app, both host app and share extension apps will be available. Share extension app will invoke only when the images are shared from external app (eg: iPhone Photos app, Google drive).</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Conclusion:</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">In order to share images to our iOS app from external apps, we should follow Approach #2. Remember that even this native iOS share extension app might crash if the image size is huge.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','How to share bigger images to iOS app using Share Extension?','','inherit','closed','closed','','231-revision-v1','','','2017-07-12 15:59:48','2017-07-12 10:29:48','',231,'http://www.divami.com/blog/231-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(233,18,'2017-07-12 16:03:17','2017-07-12 10:33:17','<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">I would like to share my experience with Share Extension. The requirement is to share images to our app from external apps like Photos/Gallery, Google Drive etc.</span>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">In hybrid apps (Cordova + Ionic), we can share images from external apps to our own app. Let’s see how to implement in iOS.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">In iOS, there is no direct way to share images from external apps to our app. In order to do that, we have to use \"<strong>iOS Share Extension</strong>\"</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><span style=\"color: #993300\"