ht: 400\">&lt;/pre&gt;\r\n</span>It’s a bit lengthy (of Course, not much).\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Using the new method </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Array.from(), </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">which was introduced in ES6, you can convert an array-like or iterable object to an array.\r\n</span>&lt;pre&gt;\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">&lt;code&gt;\r\n</span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">var elements = document.getElementsByClassName(‘***’); // returns an array-like object\r\n</span></i><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Array.from(elements); // returns an array with html nodes\r\n</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">&lt;/code&gt;\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">&lt;/pre&gt;\r\n</span>These new methods reduce our efforts a bit. Thanks for ES6 release.\r\n\r\nHappy Coding :)','Why never use new Array in Javascript?','','inherit','closed','closed','','330-revision-v1','','','2017-09-22 15:16:14','2017-09-22 09:46:14','',330,'http://www.divami.com/blog/330-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(337,22,'2017-09-22 15:17:17','2017-09-22 09:47:17','<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">When I’m playing around with Javascript array’s, I have got some weird results with an array constructor. Let’s look into it deeply..\r\n</span><b>How to create a JavaScript Array?\r\n</b>In Javascript, we can create an array using either\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Array literals or</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Array Constructor</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nLet’s start with the best way: Array Literals\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">We, as a developer, regularly use this way:\r\n</span>&lt;pre&gt;\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">&lt;code&gt;</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">var arr = [1,2,3]; // an array with three elements</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">var arr = [1]; // an array with one element</span>\r\n\r\n<span styl