r\n 	<li>How can we make the application stand out among similar products?<b>\r\n</b></li>\r\n 	<li>How will the stakeholders react to the first look of the application?<b>\r\n</b></li>\r\n 	<li>What are the odds of my designs failing? And what could be the reasons for failure?<b>\r\n</b></li>\r\n 	<li>Can I further simplify the design interactions and enhance user experience?<b>\r\n</b></li>\r\n 	<li>Is a particular feature/information worth displaying by default? Is it that important?<b>\r\n</b></li>\r\n 	<li>Have I done user research correctly? Do I know my users well enough?<b>\r\n</b></li>\r\n 	<li>How can I depict the application uniquely/ creatively?<b>\r\n</b></li>\r\n 	<li>How will I make sure that the designs are executed correctly on all resolutions?<b>\r\n</b></li>\r\n 	<li>How will I make sure I am thinking like the user and not as myself while I am designing the application?<b>\r\n</b></li>\r\n 	<li>How can I better enable developers to execute the design optimally in the given timelines?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nI believe, as designers, we need to keep asking questions at different stages of the design process. They sure will simulate our thought process for delivering optimal designs.','Some design questions that I ask myself','','publish','open','open','','design-questions-ask','','','2018-02-26 13:04:17','2018-02-26 07:34:17','',0,'http://www.divami.com/blog/?p=422',0,'post','',0),(423,17,'2018-02-23 18:59:01','2018-02-23 13:29:01','<p dir=\"ltr\">User Experience Design is an adventurous journey. It consists of series of steps, user research, interactive prototypes, typography choices, color psychology to name a few. Bringing an application to life, helping users experience the joy of using an application with ease, and ideating creatively is what really matters to me. I often ask myself lot of questions, before, during and after the Project Execution. These questions linger in my head all the time …</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>How can 