1\"><strong><span class=\"s1\">Here are the steps to create connected apps in sales force</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">    </span>Make sure the your chrome browser has \"Advanced Rest Client\" </span><span class=\"s1\">and \"ARC cookie exchange\" extensions</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">    </span>Signup for salesforce developer account at this link </span><span class=\"s1\">https://developer.salesforce.com/signup</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">    </span>After signup is done a link will be sent to your e-mail.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">    </span>Approve the link sent to e-mail and set password</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">    </span>Here password should not have any special symbols</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">    </span>Go to the below link and complete the login process</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">    </span>https://login.salesforce.com</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">    </span>After login is successfully done user specific dashboard comes up</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">    </span>Click on \"New Connected App\"</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">    </span>Under \"Basic Information\"</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">    </span>Fill in the mandatory fields marked with red</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">    </span>Under \"API\" click on checkbox \"Enable OAuth Settings\"</span></p>\r\